    "description": "System activation occurs when designated industrial hubs integrate with the Ministry of Land and the National Board of Revenue, formalizing the waterfall distribution through smart-contract enabled fiscal pipelines."
  },
  "legalConsiderations": [
    "NBR Integration: Utilizes existing Customs, VAT, and Income Tax streams as the 'Licensing Hardware' to anchor the fiscal waterfall.",
    "40/40/20 Sovereign Adaptive Waterfall: Hard-coded split ensuring 40% revenue to the Federal Government, 40% to Divisional/District Administrations, and 20% recursive reinvestment for local industrial infrastructure.",
    "Variable Quad-Partite Vetting (VQPV-BD): Governance boards structured to coordinate between federal oversight and district-level administrative execution.",
    "Fixed Cost Arbitrage: Market incentive providing a 70% land discount to firms maintaining a 95% human workforce ratio to accelerate national employment goals.",
    "Architect’s Limited Veto Provision: Non-negotiable exclusion of predatory global entities to ensure industrial sovereignty and economic stability.",
    "Statutory Irrevocability: Operational leases function as bankable interests protected against administrative disruption, ensuring continuity for federal-level tax collection."
  ],
  "benefits": {
    "@type": "ItemList",
    "itemListElement": [
      "Direct alignment with national tax-to-GDP growth targets for 2031.",
      "Automated revenue loops that provide immediate liquidity to federal and district-level administrators.",
      "Self-funded industrial infrastructure development (power, connectivity, technical vocational training) via the 20% recursive fund.",
      "High-stability environment for investment backed by sovereign-integrated industrial real estate.",
      "Creation of a permanent middle-class firewall through mandatory human-labor priority protocols."
